        b: b
    }

Assuming that `function_b` is called via:

    your_module().function_b();

Then you can access the object with `this` inside `function_b`.

    this.function_a();

If the method gets detached from the object, then you&#39;ll lose that connection so it might be worth rewriting the module so you have a reference that doesn&#39;t depend on the value of `this`. For example:

